ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Time at which assessment was started
Duration of time it takes for participant to complete screen 1 (baseline mood assessment)
Participants current anxiety
Participants current frustration level
Participants current happiness level
Participants current irritability level
Participants current difficulty concentrating level
Notes: 0 = No difficulty concentrating; 100 = High difficulty concentrating

ElementDescription: Participants current physical discomfort level
Notes: 0 = No physical discomfort; 100 = High physical discomfort

ElementDescription: Duration of time participant takes reading instructions
Easy level Star Width

Number of participant errors (Offline+Slow Errors) - Easy level
Number of times participant went outside the stars line - Easy level
Number of times participant stopped moving the mouse - Easy level
Total times around the star - Easy level
Best distance around the star as a proportion of the star perimeter - Easy level
Median distance around the star as a proportion of the star perimeter - Easy level

Number of attempts for medium difficulty
Number of total errors (Slow+Offline) during Medium difficulty task

Median distance around the star as a proportion of the star perimeter - Medium level
Number of attempts for hard difficulty
Number of total errors (Slow+Offline) during Hard difficulty task

Duration of time it takes for participant to complete screen 1 (baseline mood assessment) in milliseconds
Duration of time participant takes reading instructions in milliseconds

Amount of time participants spends on the final section (participant can quit at anytime)
